cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.DS 

This paper discusses region-based morphological image processing techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of trees and pruning criteria, which are common in machine learning and data structures, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the reconstruction process, which involves signal processing and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the preservation of contours, which is a common topic in computer graphics, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible category as well.
